Connotation = the “chemical field” around words

Denotation = literal meaning
Connotation = emotional + cultural + contextual charge

So:

Words don’t just carry meaning—they carry a field

Examples:
	•	“cheap” vs “affordable”
	•	“tax relief” vs “tax cut”
	•	“freedom fighter” vs “terrorist”

Same core idea → different activation pattern

